# 04 – Threat Register

## Purpose

This register identifies cybersecurity threats that could negatively impact information assets within the ISMS scope.

## Method Used

Threats were identified through:

- Industry threat intelligence research
- Analysis of common attacks against sports organizations
- Review of cloud and remote workforce risks
- Review of third-party vendor risks

Threat examples include:

- Phishing
- Ransomware
- Credential theft
- Insider threat
- Vendor compromise
- Social engineering

## Deliverable

Threat-Register.xlsx

## Outcome

The identified threats were later combined with organizational vulnerabilities and assets to create risk scenarios used in the formal risk assessment.

## Skills Demonstrated

- Threat identification
- Threat categorization
- Threat source analysis
- Risk assessment preparation
